# Netlify redirect rules. This file ships inside the publish directory (Vite
# copies public/ into dist/ verbatim), and Netlify processes it BEFORE any
# netlify.toml — so these rules apply no matter which config file Netlify does
# or doesn't discover. This is the authoritative copy; the netlify.toml files
# exist only as documentation/backup.
#
# 1) Proxy API calls to the backend (200 = server-side rewrite, not a redirect;
#    the trailing ! forces it). Keeps the auth cookie first-party.
/api/*  https://solitaire-wgq7.onrender.com/api/:splat  200!

# 2) SPA fallback for any other path WITHOUT force, so real static assets
#    (hashed JS/CSS, icons, sw.js) are still served normally.
/*  /index.html  200
